{"outcome":{"note":{}},"at":805829585.596078,"phase":"planning","ticketId":"23","detail":"---\n\n## Investigation Report: Issue #23 — Language-Tier Registry\n\n### 1. Project Stack & Structure\n\n- **Language:** Go 1.25.5 (`go.mod` at root)\n- **Module:** `github.com\/iksnae\/code-certification`\n- **Key dependencies:** `go-tree-sitter`, `cobra`, `golang.org\/x\/tools`\n- **Test command:** `go test .\/... -count=1`\n\n### 2. The 22 Known Language IDs\n\nSource: `internal\/discovery\/generic.go`, unexported `certifiableExts` map (line ~17–56), which is the **single source of truth** for known language file extensions:\n\n| Language ID | Extensions |\n|---|---|\n| `go` | `.go` |\n| `ts` | `.ts`, `.tsx` |\n| `js` | `.js`, `.jsx`, `.mjs`, `.cjs` |\n| `py` | `.py` |\n| `rb` | `.rb` |\n| `rs` | `.rs` |\n| `java` | `.java` |\n| `kt` | `.kt` |\n| `sh` | `.sh`, `.bash` |\n| `c` | `.c`, `.h` |\n| `cpp` | `.cpp`, `.cc`, `.cxx`, `.hpp` |\n| `cs` | `.cs` |\n| `swift` | `.swift` |\n| `php` | `.php` |\n| `elixir` | `.ex`, `.exs` |\n| `erlang` | `.erl` |\n| `scala` | `.scala` |\n| `lua` | `.lua` |\n| `r` | `.r`, `.R` |\n| `zig` | `.zig` |\n| `sql` | `.sql` |\n| `proto` | `.proto` |\n\n### 3. Capability Audit — Per-Language Collector Presence\n\n#### Structural Analyzers (registered in `internal\/analysis\/analyzer.go` init blocks)\n\n| Language | Analyzer | Parser | File |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `go` | `GoAnalyzer` | `go\/ast` | `analysis\/go_analyzer.go:33` (`init()`, `Register(\"go\",…)`) |\n| `ts` | `TSAnalyzer` | tree-sitter (typescript grammar) | `analysis\/ts_analyzer.go:24` (`init()`, `Register(\"ts\",…)`) |\n| `js` | `TSAnalyzer` | tree-sitter (same grammar) | `analysis\/ts_analyzer.go:25` (`Register(\"js\",…)`) |\n| `py` | `PythonAnalyzer` | tree-sitter (python grammar) | `analysis\/python_analyzer.go:24` (`init()`, `Register(\"py\",…)`) |\n| `rs` | `RustAnalyzer` | tree-sitter (rust grammar) | `analysis\/rust_analyzer.go:24` (`init()`, `Register(\"rs\",…)`) |\n\nNo other language has a registered analyzer. `analysis.ForLanguage(\"rb\")` returns `nil`.\n\n#### Lint Collectors (in `internal\/evidence\/executor.go` and `tools.go`)\n\n| Language | Tool(s) | Runner |\n|---|---|---|\n| `go` | `go vet`, `golangci-lint` | `executor.go:runGoVetAt`, `runGolangciLintAt` |\n| `ts`\/`js` | ESLint | `tools.go:runESLintAt` |\n| `py` | Ruff | `tools.go:runRuffAt` |\n| `rs` | cargo clippy | `tools.go:runCargoClippyAt` |\n\nNo other language has a lint runner. All lint tools are dispatched by language from `ToolExecutor.CollectAll()` in `executor.go:50-82`.\n\n#### Test Collectors\n\n| Language | Tool(s) | Runner |\n|---|---|---|\n| `go` | `go test -json` | `executor.go:runGoTestAt` |\n| `ts`\/`js` | Jest \/ Vitest | `tools.go:runJSTestAt` |\n| `py` | pytest | `tools.go:runPytestAt` |\n| `rs` | cargo test | `tools.go:runCargoTestAt` |\n\nNo other language has a test runner.\n\n#### Coverage Collectors\n\n- Go: `go test -coverprofile` → `ParseCoverProfile`\n- JS: LCOV (`ParseLCOV`) from existing `coverage\/lcov.info`\n- Python: Cobertura XML (`ParseCoberturaXML`) from existing `coverage.xml`\n- Rust: none collected (not in current code)\n\n### 4. Tier Assignments\n\n```\nTierFull (5):   go, ts, js, py, rs     — analyzer + lint + test\nTierParse (0):  (none)                   — would have analyzer but no lint\/test\nTierLint  (0):  (none)                   — would have lint but no parser\nTierGeneric(17): rb, java, kt, sh, c, cpp, cs, swift, php, elixir, erlang, scala, lua, r, zig, sql, proto\nTierNone  (0):  (none, placeholder for explicitly disabled)\n```\n\nAll languages with an analyzer (go\/ts\/js\/py\/rs) also have lint and test collectors — there is no \"Parse-only\" or \"Lint-only\" language today.\n\n### 5. Critical Implementation Detail — The Test's Dependency on Discovery\n\nThe test `TestTierRegistry_AllKnownLanguagesHaveTiers` must iterate **all known language IDs from discovery** and assert each has a tier entry. This creates a cross-package dependency:\n\n- **`certifiableExts`** (the source of truth for language→extension mapping) is **unexported** in `internal\/discovery\/generic.go`.\n- The test in `internal\/engine\/` needs access to the set of unique language IDs.\n\n**Solution needed:** Add a minimal exported function to `internal\/discovery\/generic.go`, e.g.:\n\n```go\n\/\/ KnownLanguages returns the set of all certifiable language IDs.\nfunc KnownLanguages() []string {\n    seen := make(map[string]bool)\n    for _, lang := range certifiableExts {\n        seen[lang] = true\n    }\n    langs := make([]string, 0, len(seen))\n    for lang := range seen {\n        langs = append(langs, lang)\n    }\n    sort.Strings(langs)\n    return langs\n}\n```\n\nThe test in `engine` then calls `discovery.KnownLanguages()` and checks each against the registry. This ensures CI fails when a new extension is added to `certifiableExts` without a corresponding tier entry.\n\n### 6. Existing Engine Patterns to Follow\n\n- **Package:** `package engine` at top\n- **Naming:** PascalCase exported symbols, camelCase unexported\n- **Enums:** Use `iota` like `EvidenceKind` in `domain\/evidence.go` and `SymbolKind` in `analysis\/analyzer.go`\n- **Stringer:** Map with `var tierStrings = map[Tier]string{…}` and `func (t Tier) String() string`\n- **Test pattern:** standard `go test`, table-driven tests in `_test.go` files alongside the source\n- **File layout:** The engine package currently has `certifier.go`, `pipeline.go`, `scorer.go` (+ their `_test.go` files). The new `language_tiers.go` and `language_tiers_test.go` follow the same convention.\n\n### 7. Non-Goals (from issue) — Confirmed In-Scope Boundary\n\n- ❌ No new collectors\n- ❌ No changes to `scorer.go`\n- ❌ No changes to `init_cmd.go` or report generation\n- ✅ Minimal export addition to `discovery\/generic.go` is **necessary** for the cross-package test","id":"23-868"}
